        Cash is the lifeblood of any business. When you pay upfront for a machine, that cash is gone. When you finance, you keep your cash available for day-to-day operations, payroll, inventory, and unexpected opportunities. A sudden supplier discount, an unexpected repair, or a chance to expand into a new market—all these require cash flexibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Predictable Budgeting</h3>
